# biblioHack autonomous crawl schedule — interpreted by supercronic.
# Times are UTC (container default). Each run logs to stdout: `docker logs
# bibliohack-crawler`. A shared flock (see run-job.sh) means a long nightly
# run will cause the next hourly refresh to skip rather than pile up.
#
#  ┌ minute ┌ hour ┌ dom ┌ mon ┌ dow
#  │        │      │     │     │
# Nightly catalogue growth: discover recent novedades, then ingest them.
   0        3      *     *     *   /app/run-job.sh discover_worker
# Hourly availability refresh for records whose probe is due.
   0        *      *     *     *   /app/run-job.sh refresh
